Each substring extraction is O(10) = O(1) since the length is fixed.
Adding to a HashSet is O(1) average time.
Total iterations = n−9≈O(n), where n = length of the string.
Final TC:
O(n)
💾 Space Complexity
seen set can hold up to n−9 substrings in the worst case.
Each substring has fixed length 10, so storage per substring is constant.
repeated set also holds at most n−9 substrings.
Final SC:
O(n)
